Chief Ernest Shonekan, the former head of the Interim National Government that succeeded the military junta of General Ibrahim Babangida, is dead.  Shonekan, a boardroom guru before his selection to head the Interim National Government, died in Lagos at the age of 85, according to TVC. Police declare IBB’s spokesman wantedHe was the Chairman of the interim National Government between August 26 and November 17 1993 when he was ousted in a palace coup led by late General Sani Abacha who was Secretary of Defence. Details later…  Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Head of the interim national government in Nigeria, Chief Ernest Shonekan has died at age 85. Sundiata Post recalls that Shonekan succeeded the junta of General Ibrahim Babangida. He died at Evercare hospital, in the Lekki area of Lagos state. Recall that… In "Top Stories" By Femi Ogunshola Some 18 years ago, June 8, 1998 to be precise, when the death of the then Head of State, Gen. Sani Abacha, was announced; the news elicited mixed reactions across the country. To some, the news marked the end of a ruler who ruled Nigeria with an… In "News" By Femi Ogunshola, Some 18 years ago, June 8, 1998 to be precise, when the death of the then Head of State, Gen. Sani Abacha, was announced; the news elicited mixed reactions across the country. To some, the news marked the end of a ruler who ruled Nigeria with an… In "News"